 plug in your ipod go to the photos tab and make sure that box is checked and then tell itunes where the photos folder is remember be smart always keep your virus protection updated at all times if you use a p p file sharing program ITunes Music Store Podcasting FairPlay SonicStage Windows XP Mouse (computing) Screenshot Online music store Object Desktop Apple Computer Windows 2000 Digital rights management Macintosh Finder Gmail IPod shuffle Rhythmbox Macromedia Flash AmigaOS Gramophone record PlayStation Portable Mixtape Digital audio player Apple Macintosh IPod nano Disc jockey Bluetooth System 7 (Macintosh) Minesweeper (computer game) IPhoto Apple typography RealNetworks Stardock QuickTime Visual Basic Windows registry Rhapsody (online music service) Hello world program Cascading Style Sheets Mac OS X v10.4 Uploading and downloading PHP Chess Spyware P__li Option key Commodore 64 Virtual memory Comparison of media players Xbox 360 Konqueror Beatmania IIDX Advanced Audio Coding Copy protection Getting Things Done Musical Instrument Digital Interface Internet Explorer MP3 MSN Messenger Halo 2 Enterprise content management Napster DVD Copyleft Windows Me Java programming language BitTorrent Microsoft Windows Billboard Hot 100 Google Danger Hiptop Google Desktop Windows Explorer Control Panel (Windows) Floppy disk Computer virus Sega Mega Drive/Sega Genesis Journey (band) Rootkit Pump It Up We Belong Together RealPlayer Library (computer science) 